Bit.Name: stkeyprov_ecies_attempted
Bit.Description: 0 (false): ECIES provisioning has never been attempted. 1 (true): ECIES provisioning have been attempted at least once.

Bit.Name: stkeyprov_ecies_ok
Bit.Description: Status of ECIES ST key provisioning when it was attempted. 0 (failed): ECIES ST key provisioning last attempt was failed. 1 (successful): ECIES ST key provisioning last attempt was successful.

Bit.Name: enable_fingerprint
Bit.Description: 0 (yes): fingerprint feature is disabled. 1 (no): fingerprint feature is enabled.

Bit.Name: security_counter
Bit.Description: Security counter involved in product ID for chip certificate verification by HSM-OEM in SFI context

Bit.Name: st_pub_key_id
Bit.Description: ST ECDSA public key ID (ST key instance fuse part) involved in product ID for chip certificate verification by HSM-OEM in SFI context

Bit.Name: sfi_done
Bit.Description: The SFI has been done successfully.

Bit.Name: no_data_cache
Bit.Description: 0 (enabled): DCACHE used by boot ROM. 1 (disabled): DCACHE not used by boot ROM.

Bit.Name: no_cpu_pll
Bit.Description: 0 (enabled): PLLs for CPU/AXI enabled for cold boot. 1 (disabled): PLLs for CPU/AXI not enabled for cold boot.

Bit.Name: sdmmc1_not_default_af
Bit.Description: 0 (no): SDMMC1 uses default hard coded AFmux. 1 (yes): SDMMC1 uses AFmux defined in OTP.

Bit.Name: sdmmc2_not_default_af
Bit.Description: 0 (no): SDMMC2 uses default hard coded AFmux. 1 (yes): SDMMC2 uses AFmux defined in OTP.

Bit.Name: boot0_pin_enable
Bit.Description: 0 (enabled): BOOT0 pin use is enabled. Boot ROM reads pin value to get boot0 value. 1 (disabled): BOOT0 pin use is disabled. Boot ROM uses backup register (virtual boot pin 0) to read BOOT0 pin value.

Bit.Name: boot_source
Bit.Description: If different from zero, identifies the flash memory used to boot. 1 (sdcard): SD-Card SDMMC1 2 (emmc): e.MMC SDMMC1 3 (snor): XSPI NOR 4 (snand): XSPI NAND 5 (hflash): XSPI HyperFlash 6 (pnand): FMC pNAND 7 (sdcard): SD-Card SDMMC2 8 (emmc): e.MMC SDMMC2 others: invalid

Bit.Name: boot_source_disable
Bit.Description: Each bit disables a boot source. Default to UART if all disabled. 0x01 (usb): USB boot source disabled. 0x02 (uart): UART boot source disabled. 0x04 (fdcan): FDCAN boot source disabled. 0x08 (spi): SPI boot source disabled. 0x10 (i2c): I2C boot source disabled.

Bit.Name: spi_instance_disable
Bit.Description: 0x1: SPI1 disabled 0x2: SPI2 disabled 0x3: SPI3 disabled

Bit.Name: uart_instance_disable
Bit.Description: 0x1: USART1 disabled 0x2: USART2 disabled 0x3: USART3 disabled

Bit.Name: fdcan_instance_disable
Bit.Description: 0x1: disable FDCAN1 disabled 0x2: disable FDCAN2 disabled 0x3: disable FDCAN3 disabled

Bit.Name: i2c_instance_disable
Bit.Description: 0x1: I2C1 disabled 0x2: I2C2 disabled 0x3: I2C3 disabled

Bit.Name: st_fsbl_monotonic_counter
Bit.Description: [1-0xFFFF] -> [1-32]: Value of monotonic counter is X where X is the position of the most significant bit at 1.

Bit.Name: mode0
Bit.Description: 0 (af_nopull_ls): AF; no pull; low speed. 1 (af_nopull_ms): AF; no pull; medium speed. 2 (af_nopull_hs): AF; no pull; high speed. 3 (af_pullup_ls): AF; pull up; low speed. 4 (af_pullup_ms): AF; pull up; medium speed. 5 (af_pullup_hs): AF; pull up; high speed. 6 (af_pulldown_ls): AF; pull down; low speed. 7 (af_pulldown_ms): AF; pull down; medium speed. 8 (af_pulldown_hs): AF; pull down; high speed. 9 (gpio_out_high): GPIO output high. 10 (gpio_out_low): GPIO output low. 11 (gpio_in): GPIO input 12. (gpio_open_nopull): GPIO open drain; No pull. 13 (gpio_open_pullup): GPIO open drain; pull up. 14 (gpio_open_pulldown): GPIO open drain; pull down. 15 (gpio_analog): GPIO analog mode.

Bit.Name: pin0
Bit.Description: [0-15]: pin id between 0 and 15 for GPIOA to GPIOG and GPIOP. [0-12]: pin id between 0 and 12 for GPION. [0-8]: pin id between 0 and 8 for GPIOH and GPIOQ. [0-5]: pin id between 0 and 5 for GPIOO.

Bit.Name: port0
Bit.Description: 0: reserved. 1 PA): Bank A 2 (PB): Bank B 3 (PC): Bank C 4 (PD): Bank D 5 (PE): Bank E 6 (PF): Bank F 7 (PG): Bank G 8 (PH): Bank H 9 (PN): Bank N 10 (PO): Bank O 11 (PP): Bank P 12 (PQ): Bank Q 0x15: Invalid configuration.

Bit.Name: disable_traces
Bit.Description: 0 (no): boot ROM traces disabled. 1 (yes): boot ROM traces enabled.

Bit.Name: disable_hse_freq_detect
Bit.Description: 0 (no): HSE frequency auto-detection disabled. 1 (yes): HSE frequency auto-detection enabled.

Bit.Name: disable_hse_bypass_detect
Bit.Description: 0 (no): HSE bypass detection disabled. 1 (yes): HSE bypass detection enabled.

Bit.Name: emergency_debug_req
Bit.Description: 0 (no): emergency debug not requested. 1 (yes): emergency debug requested.

Bit.Name: emmc_128k_boot_partition
Bit.Description: 0 (no): Boot ROM does not support e.MMC with 128-Kbyte boot partition. 1 (yes): Boot ROM supports e.MMC with 128-Kbyte boot partition.

Bit.Name: fsbl_decrypt_prio
Bit.Description: 0 (cryp): bootROM uses CRYP to decrypt FSBL. 1 (saes): bootROM uses SAES to decrypt FSBL.

Bit.Name: HSE_value
Bit.Description: 0x0 (auto): HSE value is auto-detected among 10, 12, 14, 16, 20, 24, 28, 32, 36, 40, and 48 MHz. 0x1: HSE = 24 MHz 0x2: HSE = 25 MHz. 0x3: HSE = 26 MHz. 0x4: HSE = 19.2 MHz. 0x5: HSE = 40 MHz. 0x6: HSE = 48 MHz. 0x7: Reserved.

Bit.Name: snand_need_plane_select_1
Bit.Description: 0 (no): serial NAND plane select not needed. 1 (yes): serial NAND plane select needed.

Bit.Name: pnand_number_of_ecc_bits_1
Bit.Description: 0 (unset): ECC unset. 1 (hamming): ECC 1 bit (Hamming). 2 (bch4): ECC 4 bits (BCH4). 3 (bch8): ECC 8 bits (BCH8). 4 (ondie): on-die ECC.

Bit.Name: pnand_bus_width_1
Bit.Description: 0 (8bits): data width is 8 bits. 1 (16bits): data width is 16 bits.

Bit.Name: nand_block_size_1
Bit.Description: [1-4]: block size in number of pages

Bit.Name: nand_page_size_1
Bit.Description: 0 (64): 64 pages per block. 1 (128): 128 pages per block. 2 (256): 256 pages per block.

Bit.Name: pnand_param_stored_in_otp
Bit.Description: 0 (no): Boot ROM uses ONFI parameter table to get parallel nand parameters. 1 (yes): parallel nand parameters are defined in bank1 or bank2, depending on nand_config_distribution value.

Bit.Name: oem_ecdsa_active_key
Bit.Description: [1-256] -> [1-8]: Value of monotonic counter is X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1. 8 possible OEM public keys (OEM key revocation feature for OEM-FSBL authentication)

Bit.Name: st_ecdsa_active_key
Bit.Description: [1-256] -> [1-8]: Value of monotonic counter is X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1. Eight possible ST public keys (ST key revocation feature for ST-FSBL authentication).

Bit.Name: secure_boot
Bit.Description: 0 (closed_openboot): device in CLOSED_OPENBOOT state. Secure boot is not enforced (OEM FSBL authentication is not mandatory). 1 (closed_secboot): device in CLOSED_SECBOOT state. Secure boot is enforced (OEM FSBL authentication is mandatory).

Bit.Name: nand_config_distribution
Bit.Description: 0 (bk1_snand_bk2_pnand): pNAND config in nand*_2 fields / sNAND config in nand*_1 fields. 1 (bk1_pnand_bk2_snand): pNAND config in nand*_1 fields / sNAND config in nand*_2 fields.

Bit.Name: dev_boot_port
Bit.Description: 0: reserved 1 (PA): Bank A 2 (PB): Bank B 3 (PC): Bank C 4 (PD): Bank D 5 (PE): Bank E 6 (PF): Bank F 7 (PG): Bank G 8 (PH): Bank H 9 (PN): Bank N 10 (PO): Bank O 11 (PP): Bank P 12 (PQ): Bank Q

Bit.Name: dev_boot_pin
Bit.Description: [0-15]: pin id between 0 and 15 for GPIOA to GPIOG, and GPIOP. [0-12]: pin id between 0 and 12 for GPION. [0-8]: pin id between 0 and 8 for GPIOH and GPIOQ. [0-5]: pin id between 0 and 5 for GPIOO.

Bit.Name: oem_fsbl_monotonic_counter
Bit.Description: [1-0xFFFF] -> [1-32]: Value of monotonic counter is X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1

Bit.Name: oem_fsbl_monotonic_counter
Bit.Description: [1-0xFFFF] -> [33-64]: Value of monotonic counter is 32+X where X is position of the most significant bit at 1

Bit.Name: A coefficient for temperature sensor 1
Bit.Description: No calibration: Â±3Â°C. Mode 1 calibration: Â±1Â°C (0 to 70) and Â±1.25Â°C (-40 to 125)

Bit.Name: A coefficient for temperature sensor 2
Bit.Description: Same in case of two temperature sensors

Bit.Name: USBTC_CCRPD1[3:0]
Bit.Description: USB Type-C CC1, 5.1 kÎ© pull-down trimming (Â±10%)

Bit.Name: USBTC_VIREF[3:0]
Bit.Description: USB Type-C CC1/CC2, ref current trimming (Â±6%)

Bit.Name: USBTC_CCRPD2[3:0]
Bit.Description: USB Type-C CC2 5.1 kÎ©, pull-down trimming (Â±10%)

Bit.Name: USE_AMBIANT
Bit.Description: Use BSEC_AMBIANT_TRIM for BSEC local oscillator

Bit.Name: BSEC_AMBIANT_TRIM[8:0]
Bit.Description: BSEC local oscillator frequency trimming at ambient temperature

Bit.Name: RST_STOP
Bit.Description: Reset caused if the device is put in Stop mode

Bit.Name: RST_STANDBY
Bit.Description: Reset caused if the device is put in Standby mode

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO5
Bit.Description: VDDIO5 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode. The I/O segment is used by SDMMC2 port.

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO4
Bit.Description: VDDIO4 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode (I/O segment used by SDMMC1 port)

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO3
Bit.Description: VDDIO3 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode (I/O segment used by XSPIM port 2)

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDDIO2
Bit.Description: VDDIO2 I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode (I/O segment used by XSPIM port 1)

Bit.Name: HSLV_VDD
Bit.Description: Main I/O segment below 2.5 V for I/O mode
